Meanwhile, Gonzalez is in his own form of prison due to to the injuries which have left him completely dependent on his wife and teenage son, and will likely never work again. That has put a serious strain on the family, since his wife also lost her job as a vice principal.

'It's gone from me being able to do pretty much whatever I want with my dad to not being able to do very much at all,' his son Jose Gonzalez Jr said. 'In fact, I have to do most things for him along with my mother.'

In addition to the planned lawsuit against J.J.'s Doghouse, the Gonzalez family settled another lawsuit against the property's owner but the terms were kept confidential.   

